    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:1.1",
          "pli": "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—",
          "en": "So I have heard. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:1.2",
          "pli": "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. ",
          "en": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:1.3",
          "pli": "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: ",
          "en": "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:1.4",
          "pli": "“bhikkhavo”ti. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants!” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:1.5",
          "pli": "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. ",
          "en": "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:1.6",
          "pli": "Bhagavā etadavoca: ",
          "en": "The Buddha said this: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:2.1",
          "pli": "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, aññatarā tāvatiṃsakāyikā devatā nandane vane accharāsaṅghaparivutā dibbehi pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitā samaṅgībhūtā paricārayamānā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: ",
          "en": "“Once upon a time, mendicants, a certain deity of the company of the Thirty-Three was amusing themselves in the Garden of Delight, escorted by a band of nymphs, and supplied and provided with the five kinds of heavenly sensual stimulation. On that occasion they recited this verse: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:3.1",
          "pli": "‘Na te sukhaṃ pajānanti, ",
          "en": "‘They don’t know pleasure "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:3.2",
          "pli": "ye na passanti nandanaṃ; ",
          "en": "who don’t see the Garden of Delight! "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:3.3",
          "pli": "Āvāsaṃ naradevānaṃ, ",
          "en": "It’s the abode of lordly gods, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:3.4",
          "pli": "tidasānaṃ yasassinan’ti. ",
          "en": "the glorious host of Thirty!’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:4.1",
          "pli": "Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, aññatarā devatā taṃ devataṃ gāthāya paccabhāsi: ",
          "en": "When they had spoken, another deity replied with this verse: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:5.1",
          "pli": "‘Na tvaṃ bāle pajānāsi, ",
          "en": "‘Fool, don’t you understand "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:5.2",
          "pli": "yathā arahataṃ vaco; ",
          "en": "the saying of the perfected ones: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:5.3",
          "pli": "Aniccā sabbasaṅkhārā, ",
          "en": "All conditions are impermanent, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:5.4",
          "pli": "uppādavayadhammino; ",
          "en": "their nature is to rise and fall; "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:5.5",
          "pli": "Uppajjitvā nirujjhanti, ",
          "en": "having arisen, they cease; "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.11:5.6",
          "pli": "tesaṃ vūpasamo sukho’”ti. ",
          "en": "their stilling is true bliss.’”"
        }
      ],
